-- Nippon Electric Glass Shares Fall Most in Three Weeks After Forecast Cut
-- B y   K y u n g   B o k   C h o
-- 2010-09-24T00:14:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/nippon-electric-glass-shares-fall-most-in-three-weeks-after-forecast-cut.html
Nippon Electric Glass Co., a
Japanese glassmaker, declined the most in three weeks in Tokyo
trading after cutting its six-month net income forecast.  Nippon Electric Glass dropped 3.5 percent to 1,091 yen as
of 9:11 a.m. on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, headed for the biggest
loss since Aug. 31. The benchmark Topix index slipped 1.1
percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyung Bok Cho at 
 kcho7@bloomberg.net  